What changes in the Python script

Since 5D added Jinja2, 5E mainly needs to make sure Jinja2 uses a real loader rooted at PXE_TEMPLATE_ROOT.

That is what allows this to work:

{% include "partials/network-dhcp.ks.j2" %}

The key script behavior should be:

Jinja2 templates render through Environment(loader=FileSystemLoader(PXE_TEMPLATE_ROOT))
includes are resolved relative to PXE_TEMPLATE_ROOT
/templates/ks/rhel8-minimal.ks.j2 can include /templates/partials/*.ks.j2
missing include fails clearly
undefined variable fails clearly
generated files still go only to /ks/*.ks

If your 5D code currently reads the template file manually and renders it from a string, includes may not work correctly. So the main 5E script change is likely inside the Jinja render function.

Conceptually it should render like this:

